<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="iddc96a66d-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee" identifier="/us/usc/t2/s282c"><num value="282c">§ 282c.</num><heading> Expenditures</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In accordance with policies and procedures approved by the Speaker, the Legislative Counsel may make such expenditures as may be necessary or appropriate for the functioning of the Office.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="iddc96a66e-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee">(<ref href="/us/pl/91/510/tV/s524">Pub. L. 91–510, title V, § 524</ref>, <date date="1970-10-26">Oct. 26, 1970</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/84/1203">84 Stat. 1203</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
